cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper proposes a novel method and protocol for establishing common secrecy between two users based on physical parameters. The paper focuses on the wireless physical layer security protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the clock frequencies, relative clock phases, and distance between users, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed protocol is also robust against various kinds of active timing attacks and active impersonating adversaries, which are related to system and control (cs.SY) and performance analysis (cs.PF).
